You have an out of the box idea, fabulous POA and your content when read by Shakespeare, he would sit and cry in the corner. But guess what, you won’t get customers.&nbsp;

You are going door to door, explaining how effective your product is for the 100th time and ready with all the possible solutions for all the impossible queries that your customers could have. But you won’t get customers.&nbsp;

![](/uploads/rte/no-you-don-t-want-to-get-customers/seo.jpg)

> Stop reading. Look around. What is the maximum number of your potential customers doing? Yes. There. Right there on their phone/ laptop screens they are waiting for you.&nbsp;

SEO- Search Engine Optimization, takes you there, the place where your potential customers have their eyeballs on- the Search Engine Result Pages (SERPs). It drives the traffic to your website by making it look gorgeous to search engines like Google, Bing, and others. With the&nbsp;

A high ranking in search results conveys authority and builds trust with users. Effective SEO practices, such as creating high-quality content, use of relevant keywords,&nbsp; on-page optimization, backlinks, ensuring fast page speeds, and optimizing for mobile devices, further strengthens user confidence.

![](/uploads/rte/no-you-don-t-want-to-get-customers/seoo.webp)

Your content is your offense. Your technique your defence. But what about the fans at the stadium? Don’t you need them to catalyze the spirit of your game? You are doing all this for yourself and for them after all. SEO brings your fans to the stadium.

Your pockets must be loaded with the funds, aren't they? No, I am not trying to be a bi***h here. Let’s say you are a richie rich and can pour ample amounts into marketing, but are unaware of SEO. Dear, you are wasting not investing. Organic traffic driven by SEO does not demand ongoing payments, unlike pay-per-click (PPC) advertising. Although it involves an initial investment in strategy, content creation, and technical enhancements, the benefits can be long-lasting.

The winning goal is the well optimized website and the right knowledge of SEO.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Well, if you are still stuck to the traditional orthodox techniques and not optimizing your websites, your competitors are. You have to adapt for your business to evolve.&nbsp;

Still stuck? I am sorry, but you won’t get customers
